
Sarah sat with her light brown eyes staring out the dirty window of the car. The rolling, flat, land went by as her anger grew. What a great surprise this is, she thought."Why so quite?" Sarah's mom asked, "I thought you would be glad about my new job.""It's hard to be glad about moving 100 miles away from my friends," Sarah mumbled under her breath. "Sarah! We are going to live by a nice little city called... well... Beach City." "What the heck? What kind of name is 'Beach City'?"After that they were quiet. Then Sarah saw a small city coming into view.